    "summary": "On 18-JUL-2018 at approximately 1630 hours, a Subsea Engineer aboard the Transocean Drillship Thalassa sustained a right knee injury while using a tagline to guide a load down to the deck in the Subsea POD shop. The engineer pulled excessively hard on the tagline while attempting to guide the load, causing the injury. A verbal risk assessment prompt card had been completed prior to the task.",
